Use the standard library
This is how to is_multiply_prime of a:
   Remember that count is 0
   Remember that d is 2
   Do this a times:
      When d is more than a, then:
         Leave the loop
      End when
      Remember that r is remainder of a and d
      When r is 0, then:
         Remember that prime is 1
         Remember that i is 2
         Do this d times:
            When i is at least d, then:
               Leave the loop
            End when
            Remember that rd is remainder of d and i
            When rd is 0, then:
               Remember that prime is 0
            End when
            Increase i
         End do
         When prime is 1, then:
            Increase count
         End when
      End when
      Increase d
   End do
   When count is 3, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   The answer is 0
Now you know
>>> is_multiply_prime of 30
1
>>> is_multiply_prime of 5
0
>>> is_multiply_prime of 30
1